Seizes Heroin, other illicit drugs in raids Operatives of the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA) have intercepted over 649,300 capsules of Tramadol 225mg and 809,850 Euros cash, among other consignments from Pakistan, Austria and Italy at the Murtala Muhammed International Airport (MMIA), Ikeja, Lagos.  MEANWHILE, Chairman/Chief Executive of NDLEA, Brig. Gen. Mohamed Buba Marwa (Retd) has commended the officers and men of the MMIA, DOGI, Kano, Adamawa and FCT Commands for the arrests and seizures.
    
He charged them and their colleagues across the country to intensify offensive action against all drug cartels in every part of Nigeria. 